Thanks for files Julian. For my version the files are different .
 Now it is working after I added below line in authorize block which adds message authenticator to the reply 

authorize {
 if (!EAP-Message) {
 update reply {
 Message-Authenticator := 0x00
 }
 }
While testing and from pam_radius usage (https://github.com/FreeRADIUS/pam_radius/blob/master/USAGE)
message_require_authenticator controls whether to honour or discard replies from radius server not having message_authenticator attribute.
It is not for controlling if the incoming Access Request should include Message authenticator or not.
It is always mandated in the Requests. The configuration changes in the PR will not control if Message Authenticator can be enabled/disabled in the Access requests.. It will knob to validate the message authenticator of the reply

require_message_authenticator - Discard Access-Accept, Access-Challenge, and
 Access-Reject packets which do not contain Message-Authenticator.

